			text="Activity 3: How might we... so that statements">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="In this activity you will identify the major areas of concern that you would like to brainstorm around, and then create 'How might we... so that' statements to define these concerns.">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="Why do this: ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;A 'How might we' statement is a way of identifying and framing the problem to be solved. Having these statements helps workshop participants to brainstorm resilience actions that are relevant, meaningful, creative, within scope of what your locality can tackle, and address root causes of resilience challenged and social vulnerability.">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="Example: 'How might we build resilience to flooding so that we can minimize the impacts on those who have the fewest resources (which neighborhoods and/or population groups)?'">
			</text>
		</textBlock>
		<textBlock>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Bold"
			text="How to do this: ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Regular"
			text="&#xD;- Get your core team together to review what you learned in Chapters 3 and 4, using the ">
			</text>
			<text
			size="16.0"
			fontFamily="System"
			fontStyle="Hyperlink"
			text="Summary of Hazards, Disasters, Threats, and Equity Issues in your community"
			linkType="internalStep"
